1
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:24,437
What's up?

2
00:00:24,797 --> 00:00:26,097
What?

3
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:28,817
Suraiyya came here,

4
00:00:28,817 --> 00:00:30,557
Met neither of us,

5
00:00:30,557 --> 00:00:33,417
And took Ammi Begum into the room.

6
00:00:33,912 --> 00:00:35,713
Who am I?

7
00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:38,548
Come.

8
00:00:38,548 --> 00:00:39,841
Where?

9
00:00:40,028 --> 00:00:41,328
Out in the sun.

10
00:00:41,328 --> 00:00:43,048
Sit for a while.

11
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:44,631
Mehru...

12
00:00:44,689 --> 00:00:47,871
When did you start talking like Ammi Begum?

13
00:00:48,369 --> 00:00:50,170
Ever since I realised

14
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:53,559
That she says only what's best.

15
00:00:54,608 --> 00:00:56,197
Merci beaucoup.

16
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:23,456
I talked to her as a mother last night.

17
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:24,960
I said,

18
00:01:25,628 --> 00:01:28,226
'You asked for time'.

19
00:01:28,566 --> 00:01:30,545
'It was our fault'

20
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:33,870
'That we didn't ask you how long you wanted'.

21
00:01:33,926 --> 00:01:36,306
She looked back, surprised.

22
00:01:36,362 --> 00:01:40,000
She couldn't believe <i>I</i> was saying that!

23
00:01:40,773 --> 00:01:42,507
Then, she said,

24
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:44,586
'About'...

25
00:01:44,686 --> 00:01:46,977
'2 or 4 days'?

26
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:51,309
I didn't stop there.

27
00:01:51,449 --> 00:01:53,260
I said, 'Even if you don't accept',

28
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:55,261
'Don't refuse'.

29
00:01:56,009 --> 00:02:01,400
Don't keep someone waiting so many years just to refuse...

30
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:06,040
Don't you think it's a job well done?

31
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,621
What about <i>him</i>?

32
00:02:11,811 --> 00:02:13,122
Who?

33
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,417
The one

34
00:02:17,807 --> 00:02:21,578
Who'll leave me tongue-tied in the doghouse.

35
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:26,178
You take care of him.

36
00:02:26,318 --> 00:02:29,768
A lad spoilt in the West can't be corrected in the East.

37
00:02:33,140 --> 00:02:36,380
As if he were ever...

38
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,477
Don't you say it?

39
00:02:38,477 --> 00:02:41,545
'Loafer, wastrel, London tramp'!

40
00:02:42,471 --> 00:02:45,861
I lie about it.

41
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,031
So that no one

42
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:51,888
Except Jiya likes him.

43
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:57,298
But you can only lie for so long before you start believing it yourself...

44
00:02:57,908 --> 00:03:01,778
I've begun to think... He's a loafer... A wastrel...

45
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,437
The London tramp!

46
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,097
Why, Ammi Begum?

47
00:03:09,302 --> 00:03:11,647
Why do you lie?

48
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,991
I hope to keep

49
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:19,097
One promise, at the very least...

50
00:03:20,580 --> 00:03:26,888
That I'm saved from being tongue-tied in the doghouse or from the doghouse if not.

51
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,828
What's going on, Maheen?

52
00:03:43,828 --> 00:03:45,838
It drives me crazy...

53
00:03:45,899 --> 00:03:48,158
I've never seen it like this!

54
00:03:48,214 --> 00:03:52,670
The Granny doesn't like it when two cousins are making peace.

55
00:03:52,730 --> 00:03:57,861
The lad's Aunt didn't let him in when he brought flowers and perfume,

56
00:03:58,011 --> 00:04:01,040
When everyone's thinking about him,

57
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:05,118
That he better be married off to someone he doesn't even love!

58
00:04:05,118 --> 00:04:07,029
What the devil is going on?

59
00:04:07,469 --> 00:04:09,438
No idea.

60
00:04:09,669 --> 00:04:11,070
But I do know

61
00:04:11,070 --> 00:04:14,407
That it'll be fine if I agreed to marry Gulrez.

62
00:04:14,497 --> 00:04:15,850
Why don't you?

63
00:04:15,850 --> 00:04:17,789
I have, Fajr.

64
00:04:18,469 --> 00:04:19,740
But my heart doesn't.

65
00:04:19,740 --> 00:04:21,169
Spiffing!

66
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:25,899
Sometimes, I begin to curse my heart.

67
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:29,539
I mean, whatever's wrong with Gulrez?

68
00:04:29,794 --> 00:04:31,099
He looks nice,

69
00:04:31,099 --> 00:04:32,512
Is of good character,

70
00:04:32,512 --> 00:04:34,169
Does his 9-to-5 job...

71
00:04:34,169 --> 00:04:35,900
Loves me, too...

72
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,481
And...

73
00:04:37,562 --> 00:04:40,002
We've been engaged since we were kids...

74
00:04:40,433 --> 00:04:42,923
What's the big deal...

75
00:04:43,613 --> 00:04:45,094
What?

76
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:49,298
No idea...

77
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:20,148
Forgive me but I don't like it one bit, Ammi Begum...

78
00:05:20,148 --> 00:05:25,501
Mum and daughter talk about everything in classified meetings,

79
00:05:25,610 --> 00:05:28,950
And Dastoor's called upon only to hear the decision.

80
00:05:29,051 --> 00:05:30,862
Put a sock in it...

81
00:05:31,283 --> 00:05:33,883
I've called you for your advice,

82
00:05:34,014 --> 00:05:36,884
Not to order you.

83
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:38,377
Leave it be.

84
00:05:38,377 --> 00:05:40,185
I know it well enough.

85
00:05:40,185 --> 00:05:46,504
I was called for 'advice' the last time as well, but it ended with an order.

86
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,908
Would you sit,

87
00:05:51,168 --> 00:05:53,514
Or would you rather that I send you out?

88
00:05:53,514 --> 00:05:55,795
Why wouldn't I sit?

89
00:05:55,887 --> 00:05:58,684
I'm someone too, after all!

90
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,708
Orders, ma'am?

91
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,928
Mehru...

92
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:08,101
I hope you remember

93
00:06:08,169 --> 00:06:10,871
What Munshi Alam Deen had said.

94
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:14,011
I do.

95
00:06:15,529 --> 00:06:17,249
He'd said,

96
00:06:17,301 --> 00:06:20,639
'If he doesn't want to marry Jiya',

97
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:24,410
'Just prod and ask him'

98
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:26,860
'Who he'd rather marry'.

99
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,664
Naw, I don't intend to prod...

100
00:06:31,878 --> 00:06:35,628
But go, Dastoor, and ask him today.

101
00:06:35,690 --> 00:06:39,878
I'm sure his answer will put you on the rack.

102
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:53,149
You're very angry with me, yes?

103
00:06:53,657 --> 00:06:55,947
Because I didn't obey you?

104
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:01,968
You think I've left you helpless?

105
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:08,457
No, Dado...

106
00:07:08,998 --> 00:07:13,590
As for my respect and regard for you, I can sacrifice my life for you.

107
00:07:13,590 --> 00:07:15,789
Cut to the chase...

108
00:07:18,424 --> 00:07:19,900
What do I say?

109
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:28,667
I've been asking myself why I just couldn't obey you.

110
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,998
Why I just can't marry Jiya...

111
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:40,961
But I've realised today

112
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,078
That I will never marry Jiya.

113
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,018
Who, then?

114
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:05,480
Aye, who'd you rather marry? I want a name!

115
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,052
Maheen.

116
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:12,976
It's been so long!

117
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:15,417
Why are you so late?

118
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:20,438
Gulrez wasn't well.

119
00:09:20,598 --> 00:09:22,776
He took a pill and went to bed.

120
00:09:24,381 --> 00:09:29,921
I was worried about what I'd do alone if things got bad.

121
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:37,867
No...

122
00:09:39,410 --> 00:09:41,780
But you always drink a glass of water...

123
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:43,987
First thing you get back...

124
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,767
What are you looking at?

125
00:09:49,825 --> 00:09:51,377
What happened?

126
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,310
Sit.

127
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:13,724
Dad used to say...

128
00:10:15,128 --> 00:10:19,368
A mother's heart can also be found in daughters and sisters.

129
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,611
But I don't think any mother

130
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:25,957
Would be so motherly as you.

131
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:29,109
So?

132
00:10:31,069 --> 00:10:33,389
Which is why I'm sometimes afraid of you.

133
00:10:38,090 --> 00:10:39,947
Please, don't fear me...

134
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:42,905
Or the mother in me.

135
00:10:44,617 --> 00:10:46,938
Just speak your heart out.

136
00:10:47,468 --> 00:10:49,528
You wouldn't be able to hear it.

137
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:52,966
I'm a mother, yes?

138
00:10:53,945 --> 00:10:55,718
Let me tell you

139
00:10:57,490 --> 00:11:01,198
That the Lord gives mothers courage unlike any other.

140
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:10,540
C'mon!

141
00:11:10,678 --> 00:11:13,319
The worry kills me!

142
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:23,948
Waqar Ahmed has made it clear that he'll marry Maheen.

143
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,810
So?

144
00:11:33,810 --> 00:11:34,965
I mean --

145
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:39,507
As if Waqar Ahmed's words are a Royal edict

146
00:11:39,597 --> 00:11:41,867
That must be followed!

147
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,487
Aye.

148
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,749
It <i>is</i> a Royal edict now.

149
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:49,409
That's what we've been fearing.

150
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:50,413
We?

151
00:11:50,413 --> 00:11:51,850
All of us.

152
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:54,898
Uncle Dastoor, Aunt Suraiyya, me...

153
00:11:55,198 --> 00:11:57,538
And, most of all, Ammi Begum...

154
00:11:58,068 --> 00:12:01,686
We've tried our best to make sure it never comes to this...

155
00:12:02,358 --> 00:12:04,269
But, in all honesty,

156
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:06,960
No amount of wits and wisdom can change

157
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,620
What's willed.

158
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:15,177
But she said she loves no one else!

159
00:12:19,460 --> 00:12:22,628
She spoke her heart out then.

160
00:12:24,330 --> 00:12:27,159
She doesn't love Gulrez.

161
00:12:45,080 --> 00:13:00,580
♪ <i>In the tale of love where do these turns come from...</i> ♪

162
